The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Mishaps claim three
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Mishaps claim three
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Three men died and 11 were injured in four road mishaps in the city on Friday.        
	An unidentified man in his 20s was run over by a vehicle on Diamond Harbour Road on Friday morning. He was taken to SSKM Hospital where he was declared dead.        
	Samir Basu, 60, died after being hit by a private bus at the Hatibagan crossing around 8.30pm. He was pronounced dead at RG Kar hospital. A mob beat up the driver, who was admitted to the same hospital.        
	Biharilal Sau, 42 died after being hit by a lorry near Bagbazar ghat in the evening. The driver fled.        
	Two pavement dwellers were injured when a Tata Sumo hit them after colliding with a goods vehicle at the MG Road-College Street crossing on Friday morning. Subhas Majumder, 50, was injured after being knocked down by a private bus at the Shyambazar five-point crossing around 1pm. The bus driver was arrested at the Sinthee crossing.        
	In Howrah, eight farmers were injured after the mini-truck they were travelling in overturned near Junglepur on NH6 on Friday afternoon.        
	Liquor arrest: Three people were arrested from Chhainabhi area in Salt Lake late on Thursday night for illegally selling foreign liquor from a grocery shop. Seventy-five bottles of liquor were seized from the shop.        
	Mill trouble: Workers of Jagaddal Jute Mill in Barrackpore ransacked the Citu and Intuc offices outside the main gate on Friday morning after the management put up a suspension of work notice.                                                                                                                                                          
